@startuml fig-A02-message-flow
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

title IDS — E2 PCAP Flow (Scan Detection and Payload Alert)

participant "h1\n(attacker)" as ATK #FFCDD2
participant "s1" as SW #BBDEFB
participant "h2\n(victim)" as VIC #C8E6C9
participant "IDS Engine" as IDS #E1BEE7
participant "tcpdump" as CAP #ECEFF1

== SCAN EPISODE (time window = 5 s) ==

ATK -[#E53935]> SW : SYN → port 22
SW -> VIC : SYN → port 22
VIC --> SW : RST (closed)
ATK -[#E53935]> SW : SYN → port 80
SW -> VIC : SYN → port 80
VIC -[#43A047]-> SW : SYN-ACK (open)
ATK -[#E53935]> SW : SYN → port 443
SW -> VIC : SYN → port 443
VIC --> SW : RST (closed)
note right of ATK : repeated for >=10\ndistinct ports

IDS -> IDS : aggregate: >=N SYNs\nto different ports in 5 s
IDS -[#E53935]> IDS : emit SCAN alert (JSON)
note right of IDS #FFCDD2 : R1: tcp.flags.syn==1 && ack==0 >= 10\nR2: tcp.flags.reset==1 >= 1

== PAYLOAD SIGNATURE ==

ATK -> SW : HTTP GET /search?q=DROP TABLE
SW -> VIC : forwarded
IDS -> IDS : match substring "DROP TABLE"
IDS -[#E53935]> IDS : emit PAYLOAD alert (JSON)
note right of IDS #FFCDD2 : R3: tcp.len>0 && frame\ncontains "GET " >= 1

== EVIDENCE ==

SW -> CAP : traffic_e2.pcap
IDS -> CAP : alerts.jsonl + summary.md

legend right
  Two alert classes demonstrated:
  1. Port scan via SYN threshold
  2. Payload signature via substring match
  Each alert links to concrete PCAP packets.
endlegend
@enduml
